With this thorough website launch checklist,

00:00:15.720 --> 00:00:17.895
you can be confident that you have ticked

00:00:17.895 --> 00:00:22.545
all the boxes and your website is ready for the short time.

00:00:22.545 --> 00:00:26.520
There are a series of common task that you need to

00:00:26.520 --> 00:00:30.310
perform to get every website ready to launch.

00:00:30.310 --> 00:00:35.330
It is basically the best practices that every website needs to follow.

00:00:35.330 --> 00:00:36.830
Let us see the list.

00:00:36.830 --> 00:00:39.545
Number one is to check for the homepage.

00:00:39.545 --> 00:00:45.290
Check whether you have correctly assigned the homepage as home in the reading Settings.

00:00:45.290 --> 00:00:50.015
Number 2 is to make sure that you have deleted all the dummy content

00:00:50.015 --> 00:00:54.590
and Lorem Ipsum that came with the templates or sample pages.

00:00:54.590 --> 00:01:00.695
In fact, cleaned the list of pages and post and remove all the unwanted ones.

00:01:00.695 --> 00:01:05.540
Next is to deactivate or delete the unwanted plug-ins.

00:01:05.540 --> 00:01:09.155
Next is to double-check the permalink settings

00:01:09.155 --> 00:01:13.220
for URL structure that is set to post name.

00:01:13.220 --> 00:01:16.685
Next is to check the admin email address as

00:01:16.685 --> 00:01:19.700
all the important communication and form submission data

00:01:19.700 --> 00:01:22.700
will be received on this e-mail. Only.

00:01:22.700 --> 00:01:25.475
Next is to check the time zone.

00:01:25.475 --> 00:01:30.605
Next is to check whether the search engine indexing is not blocked.

00:01:30.605 --> 00:01:35.615
Next one is to cross-check the comments settings.

00:01:35.615 --> 00:01:40.505
Next is to check the site title and description.

00:01:40.505 --> 00:01:45.215
Next is to check the fav icon or site icon.

00:01:45.215 --> 00:01:52.020
Next one is to check the forms for submission using some tests entries.

00:01:52.150 --> 00:01:57.335
Next one is to create a custom 400 four page.

00:01:57.335 --> 00:02:01.940
Okay, so what does a 400 four page is the page that is shown

00:02:01.940 --> 00:02:06.710
when the visitor enters some link that does not exist on your website.

00:02:06.710 --> 00:02:12.245
You can easily create this using Elementor team builder by going to add new template,

00:02:12.245 --> 00:02:14.480
selecting Error 400 four page,

00:02:14.480 --> 00:02:15.635
giving it a name,

00:02:15.635 --> 00:02:21.335
designing it, publishing it by adding condition 404 page, that's it.

00:02:21.335 --> 00:02:29.390
Next is to set up a redirection of old URLs to new URLs using the redirection plugin.

00:02:29.390 --> 00:02:34.175
This is an optional one and use this only if required.

00:02:34.175 --> 00:02:42.125
Next is to ensure that SSL certificate is valid and URLs have HTTPS as protocol.

00:02:42.125 --> 00:02:45.440
Next is to verify whether all the internal links

00:02:45.440 --> 00:02:48.605
are working fine and data no broken links.

00:02:48.605 --> 00:02:51.620
This is very important from the SEO point of view.

00:02:51.620 --> 00:02:57.080
For this, you can use a Chrome extension called as SEO money on.

00:02:57.080 --> 00:03:02.210
Next is to check for the SEO title and Meta descriptions.

00:03:02.210 --> 00:03:05.270
Well, you can easily set the title and description

00:03:05.270 --> 00:03:09.125
for each webpage using the Yoast SEO plug-in.

00:03:09.125 --> 00:03:14.435
Next is to test the visitor data in Google Analytics.

00:03:14.435 --> 00:03:20.705
Next is to submit the sitemap and Google Search Console for indexing the site.

00:03:20.705 --> 00:03:25.099
You can copy the sitemap length from the general settings of Yoast SEO,

00:03:25.099 --> 00:03:30.665
then selecting features, clicking on the question eigen near XML sitemaps,

00:03:30.665 --> 00:03:31.895
clicking on the link,

00:03:31.895 --> 00:03:33.770
see the XML sitemap.

00:03:33.770 --> 00:03:38.600
Here, copy the slug only and log onto Google Search Console.

00:03:38.600 --> 00:03:43.130
Click on sitemaps and paste the slug. Click on Submit.

00:03:43.130 --> 00:03:48.905
That's the process to request for crawling and indexing the website on Google.

00:03:48.905 --> 00:03:55.160
Next is to ensure the e-mail marketing tool setup and integration with forms.

00:03:55.160 --> 00:03:59.075
Next is to check for the setup of legal pages.

00:03:59.075 --> 00:04:02.180
Although it depends on the legal requirement and

00:04:02.180 --> 00:04:05.405
jurisdiction of the country or place you are working.

00:04:05.405 --> 00:04:09.500
But still it is recommended to at least have the privacy policy page on

00:04:09.500 --> 00:04:14.525
the website and updated on the privacy settings as well.

00:04:14.525 --> 00:04:19.700
Next is to check and optimize a website for performance by testing

00:04:19.700 --> 00:04:24.890
the load time on GT metrics or Pingdom or Google PageSpeed Insights.

00:04:24.890 --> 00:04:27.215
In case the load time is higher,

00:04:27.215 --> 00:04:29.990
you can follow the suggestions to reduce the load time

00:04:29.990 --> 00:04:33.425
that we discussed in the previous lesson.

00:04:33.425 --> 00:04:36.770
Next is to have a backup plan to keep

00:04:36.770 --> 00:04:40.235
a copy of the website in case something bad happens,

00:04:40.235 --> 00:04:43.280
make sure the backup should use is working.

00:04:43.280 --> 00:04:48.770
Next is to secure the website using security plugins if required.

00:04:48.770 --> 00:04:52.055
Next is to make sure you activate the license of

00:04:52.055 --> 00:04:55.760
premium plugins for auto update feature to work.

00:04:55.760 --> 00:05:00.185
And the final checkpoint is to best,

00:05:00.185 --> 00:05:03.320
best handed test a lot on

00:05:03.320 --> 00:05:09.365
different browsers and devices to ensure that everything is working fine.

